==English==
My name is Kevin. Kevin is a good name, because I'm a pretty cool guy. After all, I'm named Kevin. I think that more people should be named Kevin. It seems to have a certain ring to it. Not to mention, naming your son Kevin will undoubtedly make him irresistable to the ladies. Yes, they love a good Kevin. 

===Pronunciation===
*kĕ'vĭn, /ˈkɛvɪn/, /<tt>"kEvIn</tt>/

===Etymology===
From Irish ''[[Caoimhín]]'', from [[Old Irish]] ''[[Coemgen]]'', comely birth

===Proper noun===
'''Kevin''' (''plural:'' '''Kevins''')
# A male [[given name]].
# (''UK derogatory slang'') A [[working-class]] male.

